<p>In truth regarding <span style="background-color:#d3d3d3" id="select">and plain truth be told, rows on such matters aren't exactly rare in my household. I despise <a href=http://trilema.com/2011/howl-de-alan-ginsberg/>Ginsburg</a>, as a forinstance, also deeply respected, perhaps in some different proportion for the same reasons</span> (nor do I agree there's <em>any</em> merit whatsoever to the intolerable</a> jew<sup><a href="#footnote_7_94724" id="identifier_7_94724" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="And, incidentally, what the fuck is with all these `angles` and `heavens` all the fucking time, what is this colonial crap ? If it's poetry it gotta be with angels just like if it's a `serious` biker's outfit` it'd better have rivets ?
Fucking spare me, if you do word density counts on the foreign material included in Trilema articles discussing outsiders, and then ignore the supposed `meaning` (implicit, decontextualized, like marketeering idiots think words work) of the their wordage there captured, you discover that militant idiots aren't distinguishable from `poets` on this basis : different selection of `meaningful` symbols, but used in the same manners, vomited in the same patterns, out-and-out substitution could turn a health guru into a modernist poet and back into a reformist presbyterian mechanically, because they're structurally identical -- and all of it, of course, very self-evidently Made in the USA. All cut off the same (and slightly stained, in the family way) bedsheet cloth, all the same `reverend` fireband-itinerant preacher at heart, three people in a boat pretending to countryhood and shipship, fucking forget about it.">viii</a></sup>, entirely undistinguished nor distinguishable from any <a href=http://trilema.com/2016/and-they-wont-fucking-yield/>other such abject object</a>) ; whereas nobody even heard before of the poetry <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/lili-marleen-the-only-english-version-that-doesnt-suck/>I care about</a>.</p>
<p>Yet the idea, the titular idea, the idea owning the world as well as lending us our title is not exactly novel, nor is it exactly dead. Let's read together : </p>
<blockquote><p>The kings of France and Scotland,<br />
bishops William of St. Andrews, William of Glasgow, William of Aberdeen, Richard of Dunkeld, Martin of Argyle, Adam of Brechin, and Maurice of Dunblane. </p>
<p>Signification that although Elizabeth Mor and Isabella Boutellier, noble damsels of the diocese of Glasgow, are related in the third and fourth degrees of kindred, Robert Steward of Scotland, lord of Stragrifis, in the diocese of Glasgow, the king's nephew, carnally knew first Isabella, and afterwards, in ignorance of their kindred, Elizabeth, who was herself related to Robert in the fourth degree of kindred, living with her for some time and having many children of both sexes by her; the above king and bishops therefore pray the pope that for the sake of the said offspring, who are fair to behold (aspectibus gratiose), to grant a dispensation to Robert and Elizabeth to intermarry, and to declare their offspring legitimate.</p>
<p>To be granted by the diocesan, at whose discretion one or more chapelries are to be founded by Robert.<br />
Avignon, 10 Kal. Dec. 1347</p></blockquote>
